cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a model of decision-making in groups that is rooted in Bayesian inference but also incorporates heuristics and dual-process psychological theories. The paper focuses on analyzing the implications of the information structure and probability distributions on the decision outcomes. Given the focus on decision-making and probability, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.SI and cs.LG. The paper also touches on game theory (cs.GT) and data structures (cs.DS) in its analysis of the decision outcomes.
